    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-quality 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This chassis remains in a pristine state of preservation, retaining its factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution and sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension. The power delivery is seamless, with the secondary turbocharger articulating perfectly at 4,500 RPM. Recent preventative maintenance includes a full vacuum line overhaul using high-temp silicone, a refreshed cooling stack with a multi-pass aluminum radiator, and verified compression numbers that meet original factory tolerances across all rotor faces. The Torsen limited-slip differential and synchronized five-speed manual transmission operate with mechanical perfection. No signs of thermal degradation or structural oxidation; this is a definitive collector-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
